This paper is primarily focused on the problem of zero-shot learning in computer vision, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a novel generative model that combines visual and semantic information, which is a common theme in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The model also uses adversarial training, which is a popular technique in both computer vision and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper evaluates the model's performance on image classification tasks, which is a common application of multimedia (cs.MM).
